Description: From the publisher: "Darkness covers the earth, and the world is under the control of evil." Who will rise up to fight for good?
Title: NAOKI URASAWA'S 20TH CENTURY BOYS, VOL. 19
Author: Naoki Urasawa

Description: Troubled by spirits that only he can see, Watanuki Kimiharo strikes a Faustian bargain with an alluring witch to get rid of them.
Title: XXXHOLIC, VOL. 19
Author: Clamp

Description: Welcome to Todo High, whose student body is composed of the toughest of brawlers.
Title: TENJO TENGE: FULL CONTACT EDITION 2-IN-1, VOL. 5
Author: Oh Great

Description: The Pokemon saga continues with the introduction of two new trainers: Black and White.
Title: POKEMON BLACK AND WHITE, VOL. 5
Author: Hidenori Kusaka

Description: Welcome to life in Ikebukuro, a Japanese city with lots of unusual activity, including the Black Biker, who is rumored to be headless.
Title: DURARARA!!, VOL. 1
Author: Ryohgo Narita and Akiyo Satorigi
Contributor: by Ryohgo Narita and Akiyo Satorigi

Description: Negi, the boy wizard, learns he will be teaching English at an all-girls high school in Japan, but he must keep his powers a secret.
Title: NEGIMA! MAGISTER NEGI MAGI, VOL. 33
Author: Ken Akamatsu

Description: Another Romeo and Juliet tale: Mizuki is the the lead guitarist in an all-girl rock band. Akira is from an all-boy school and wants to join. Can they become band mates and something more?
Title: AI ORE: LOVE ME, VOL. 4
Author: Mayu Shinjo

Description: This series is about grade-school boys who want to become professionals in the manga industry. In this volume, the boys face some fierce competition.
Title: BAKUMAN, VOL. 9
Author: Tsugumi Ohba

Description: Sailor Moon fights for justice in the name of the Moon and the mysterious Moon Princess. Along the way, she recruits other girls to be Sailor Scouts and join her fight against evil.
Title: SAILOR MOON, VOL. 3
Author: Naoko Takeuchi

Description: Naruto, who wants to be a great ninja, is locked in a battle to decide the fate of the land.
Title: NARUTO, VOL. 54
Author: Masashi Kishimoto
